        <h2 MadCap:conditions="RN-TEAM-ONLY.n-only"><a name="Early-2203"></a>Early Access Features</h2>
        <!-- 
			The items in this snippet should all be new.
			This snippet will show up in both the Monthly EA section and the EA page. 
			The H2 heading is conditioned n-only so it can be excluded from the EA page. 
			-->
        <h3 MadCap:conditions="RN-TEAM-ONLY.n-only">New Features</h3>
        <div>
            <h4>Automatically update public keys in the Admin Console</h4>
            <p MadCap:conditions="Primary.do-not-publish">Product - OIE Product</p>
            <p MadCap:conditions="Primary.do-not-publish">OAUTH2_CLIENT_CREDENTIALS_JWKS_URI_ENABLED EA&#160;2022.03.0</p>
            <p>Using <span class="code">private_key_jwt</span> as your app's client authentication method requires that you upload public keys to Okta and then use the private keys to sign the assertion. Then, you must update the client configuration each time you rotate the key pairs. This is time-consuming and error-prone. To seamlessly use key pairs and rotate them frequently, you can now configure <span class="code">private_key_jwt</span> client authentication in the Admin Console for OAuth clients by specifying the URI where you store your public keys.  See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Apps/oauth-client-cred-mgmt.htm">Manage secrets and keys for OIDC&#160;apps</MadCap:xref>.</p>
        </div>
        <h3 MadCap:conditions="RN-TEAM-ONLY.n-only">Enhancements</h3>
        <div>
            <h4>Incremental Imports for the Org2Org app</h4>
            <p MadCap:conditions="Primary.do-not-publish">Product - OIE Product </p>
            <p MadCap:conditions="Primary.do-not-publish">PROV_ORG2ORG_INCREMENTAL_IMPORTS EA 2022.03.0</p>
            <p>Okta now supports incremental imports for the Org2Org app. Incremental imports improve performance by only importing users that were created, updated, or deleted since your last import.

		See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Provisioning/org2org/org2org-main.htm">[%=okta-variables.ProductName%] Org2Org</MadCap:xref>.</p>
        </div>
    </body>
